Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.47,0:00:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you are the Black King and his subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.77,0:00:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you would destroy the humans.\NYou boasted so boldly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.65,0:00:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tamed the winged dragons that we ruled,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and treated them like your own pets...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.45,0:00:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are underestimating us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.25,0:00:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the Black King.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.87,0:00:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you intend to join my alliance,\Nyou may take your place in line.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.54,0:00:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you speak in such an arrogant\Nmanner to this Bronze Dragon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.09,0:00:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell you think you are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.97,0:00:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.22,0:00:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It matters not to me whoever \Nor whatever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.98,0:00:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To me, you are no different\Nfrom a single starving Goblin child.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.11,0:00:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look over here, you ragged fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.86,0:00:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall tear you into \Nrags to match your robe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.67,0:01:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.10,0:01:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you follow us, or \Nwill you die with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.93,0:01:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may no longer stand on the fence, Bronze.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.35,0:01:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Respond to me, Bronze!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.81,0:01:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cease! Stop! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.28,0:01:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, the alliance...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.78,0:01:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will join your alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.33,0:01:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I welcome you, Bronze.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.96,0:01:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have now become one who is scorned\Nrather than one who is feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hence, you have the right \Nto join my alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:01:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such dreadful power.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.09,0:02:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is high praise coming from\Na quiet man like you, Hijikata.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.52,0:02:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power of our Black Lord\Nis the replication of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.10,0:02:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His healing power is one derivation of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.61,0:02:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, uncontrolled reproduction could\Nresult in cancerous growth, leading to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.16,0:02:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--B-Black Lord!\N--Black Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.37,0:02:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.66,0:02:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to prostrate\Nyourselves before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.67,0:02:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me some room to make use of my power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.23,0:02:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can replicate anything\Nthat is animate ad infinitum...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,....cells, even food...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To those who stand against the Black King,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:03:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,recognizing him as the commander\Nof the opposing force,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his power must be nothing\Nshort of a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.66,0:03:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can instantly cure those who are injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.37,0:03:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even those who would be beyond recovery\Nor facing death under normal circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.96,0:03:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could return to the front lines in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can create food and firewood infinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The concept of logistics falls apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, why does he have\Nthem cultivate the earth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't he just create food himself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.76,0:03:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.10,0:03:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I am not God, who possesses eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Black Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.52,0:03:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rasputin, is it completed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.36,0:03:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was a professional, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.07,0:03:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The system is extremely simple, but the\Nsimplicity should work better for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.16,0:03:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I chose an eye for our symbol.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Starting with the concept of fire worship,\Nand mixing in other ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from Varuna, Egyptian and Celtic mythos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I combined the best parts of\Nthese ideas to compose this system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.00,0:04:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, these were...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...copied from the Latin alphabet...\NWell, actually, this is the Latin alphabet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.88,0:04:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, it may take a long time\Nto make them understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.55,0:04:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have planned?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.43,0:04:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are a multi-racial community.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobolds. Goblins. And we will become\Neven more diverse in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to unite these races.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will create our own writing system,\Nunify their religions, and educate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Primitive agriculture, a new\Nwriting system, unified religion...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They, who have been teased\Nby being called monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will take the place of humans and forge\Ntheir own civilization in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.25,0:04:42.92,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Act 10\NBaba Yatu"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We gather all the soil collected from villages,\Nstore it in the former administrative office first...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or if each village can bring it to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.52,0:04:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then we have this many horses\Nand this much wheat...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.56,0:04:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.69,0:04:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my God! Cherry Boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:04:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Oh my God!\N--Well, it's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.98,0:05:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me that, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.57,0:05:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A strange carriage is approaching here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.29,0:05:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A strange... carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.95,0:05:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is Count Saint-Germi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.04,0:05:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a powerful aristocrat from Orte!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Elven boys, go hide now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You Elven girls, no need to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.09,0:05:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.84,0:05:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.26,0:05:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.31,0:05:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place looks incredibly dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.12,0:05:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly does.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.13,0:05:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This really isn't what I was expecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I imagined some place more\Ntwinkling and glittering...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.32,0:05:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brilliant sunlight filtering\Nthrough the leaves of trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.14,0:05:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A forest where a hidden, \Nholy spring is gushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.40,0:05:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, the naked Elven boys\Nplaying with the spirits of dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.43,0:05:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,frolicking and laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your mouths!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:55.41,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dreamy" "Dreamy"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.42,0:05:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saint-Germi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:06:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you personally\Ncome to a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who on earth are you? A Drifter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.92,0:06:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Mills, the former tax\Naccountant of the Elven colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.04,0:06:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the Elves have locked me up and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, you look like a virgin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to see the Drifters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.94,0:06:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They must be here, right?!\NBring them here... Bring the Drifters!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That's right. Bring them to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.88,0:06:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are only a few Elven boys here?!\NYou must be hiding them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring them out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.61,0:06:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... actually... they are\Nnot here at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?! Where are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.41,0:06:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must confess. Or else, \NI will eat you alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I'm sowwy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.04,0:06:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-They told me they were going to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.58,0:06:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,free the Dwarves and took \Nthe Elven men with them...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.33,0:06:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and, um... that the \NDwarves... would make them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.37,0:06:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,firearms, machine guns, and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.09,0:06:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.38,0:06:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Di... Di... Did you say they were going\Nto have the Dwarves make firearms?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh... Wh... What...\NWhat about black powder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:06:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They already have black powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.34,0:07:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are continuously \Nmaking a large quantity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.19,0:07:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over. Orte is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Muket? What the heck is a muket?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.83,0:07:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it edible?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.58,0:07:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Musket! It's called a musket!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been doing anything besides eating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can fight as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring us more booze and food!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, you guys recovered\Nway too quickly after you ate!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.25,0:07:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh?!\N--You wanna fight, idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should've been tons\Nof food in this arsenal...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.30,0:07:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu, we just got an additional order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.82,0:07:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Soup for a hundred people!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of place do they think this is?!\NJust serve them water!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.32,0:07:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more they eat,\Nthe more muscular they become.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary... Dwarves really are scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.80,0:08:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.95,0:08:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that? Why are you smiling, Shara?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.00,0:08:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.79,0:08:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dwarves are back. The Dwarves\Nfrom our bedtime stories are back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.43,0:08:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't "Ahhh" me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... hey, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.69,0:08:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that guy Yoshitsune?\NHe's a horrible person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.11,0:08:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am... I am listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So here is the thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.87,0:08:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly, he was like, "Shoot the fan!"\NThat didn't make any sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.58,0:08:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way in hell I could hit the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.79,0:08:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he really think I could shoot a sailor?!\NHe's got to be out of his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.13,0:08:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take that crap anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's some nasty booze.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put your clothes back on.\NYou may give them the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.96,0:09:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right... Show me this "musket" thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.27,0:09:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.49,0:09:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ain't gonna break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.40,0:09:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? It's an iron cylinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.15,0:09:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it's made of rolled iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The trigger mechanism seems to be similar\Nto that of a crossbow. Simple enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.16,0:09:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does the spring cause this iron bit\Nto drop down onto the metal pan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that do? Is this\Nsome sort of projectile device?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.88,0:09:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The base is made of just regular wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.05,0:09:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what on earth is this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. It's a weapon called a musket.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gunpowder is ignited in the cylinder,\Npropelling a lead bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.14,0:09:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying this is a weapon that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...launches a lead bullet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any idea about the\Ngunpowder or that sort of thing, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.49,0:09:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...why go through so much\Neffort for such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't bows and crossbows just as good?\NWhat is so special about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.16,0:10:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On that point, I don't \Nfully understand either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.42,0:10:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bows won't make any sound\Nor require any development.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.63,0:10:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, why a musket?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.71,0:10:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.88,0:10:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...both sound and smoke are necessary.\NHow should I put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.89,0:10:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The roar of the musket is its battle cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A musket has a voice of\Nits own when aimed at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.06,0:10:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, it is quick to train with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.48,0:10:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the span of a day, a peasant can\Nbe trained to kill veteran soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.15,0:10:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm... It is as I thought, he is no fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.86,0:10:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, battle is the only thing he knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.61,0:10:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A musket has long range\Nand commanding power,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.57,0:10:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that's not the only \Nreal advantage it holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It also simplifies killing, soothes\Nmurderous intent, and relieves guilty emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.25,0:10:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, with only a single pull,\Nanyone can be a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a path for all civilians \Nto become warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.17,0:11:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell them that. No way... I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.18,0:11:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At last you have awoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.15,0:11:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm at...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.23,0:11:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Northern Walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.98,0:11:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were retrieved by dragon cavalry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.03,0:11:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Gilles De Rais?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.78,0:11:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dead... Became a lump of salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.62,0:11:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your intent?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am going! I'll burn those bastards!\NI'll kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not. You underestimated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't take the Drifters lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.84,0:11:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time I will kill them!\NI will be sure to kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.76,0:11:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take revenge for Gilles de Rais!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.63,0:11:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.39,0:11:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will wait for your chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.31,0:11:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For, in the end, I will certainly\Nensure your desire comes to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.02,0:11:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:12:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will kill that samurai bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.69,0:12:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will thoroughly burn him to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.61,0:12:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will burn him until not \Neven his ashes remain!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go... with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.35,0:12:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has awoken at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.37,0:12:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is doing well considering\Nher skull was almost split.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.12,0:12:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Black Lord healed her wound,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.96,0:12:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it wouldn't have been strange\Nif she had died before arriving here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Drifter leader named Toyohisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He does not seem the type to stay his hand\Njust because his enemy is a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.60,0:12:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps... he went easy on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.02,0:12:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He held back, but he stopped\Nbefore the final blow was struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't care what\Nwould happen afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His existence itself is an\Nembodiment of complacency.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that is what "samurai" is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For this reason alone, we \Ncan't underestimate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 800 years since\Ntheir feudal system was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.83,0:12:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those mere thugs can think of nothing\Nbut killing each other on such tiny islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.16,0:13:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Russia lost to their \Ndescendants, didn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.18,0:13:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're angry because Joan\Nwas bullied, aren't you, princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.89,0:13:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have not been angered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.44,0:13:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cease!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have them cease!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black King, stop this! Have them cease!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Cease this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.25,0:13:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you cannot walk beside us,\Nyou are mere meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep this to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.81,0:13:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.86,0:14:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That damn jackass is pretending\Nto be a government official...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...while he is only a social worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way in hell he will\Nstand a chance against me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.25,0:14:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.67,0:14:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about the iron cylinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.71,0:14:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You told me it was called \Na musket, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blacksmiths of your\Ncountry are pretty skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.68,0:14:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they are no match for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here is the first one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh--?! Don't tell me you finished already.\NIt's only been a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.11,0:14:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If just a plan had been provided,\Nit would've been different. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we have the real thing. There is no\Nreason it couldn't be done quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.36,0:14:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try it. There shouldn't \Nbe any problem with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we bring the production up\Nto full force in this castle town,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.96,0:15:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how many can we make?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.31,0:15:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This town provided more than half\Nof the Orte's armaments.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.09,0:15:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was while we were starved and lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.73,0:15:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If all of us work at full force, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be same as making swords or armor,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.54,0:15:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it will take some time to get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.38,0:15:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can start out with seven to eight muskets,\Nthen maybe we can increase to ten...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.94,0:15:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all?! You were so\Nfull of confidence earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.74,0:15:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that enough?! We can only manage\Nto make ten muskets per day at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.03,0:15:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be unreasonable!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.99,0:15:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Per day?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.58,0:15:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Dwarf serious?! That's incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an evil look!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.33,0:15:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He gets that way every now on then.\NPlease ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, where did Toyohisa go?\NIs he eating again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where he went.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.30,0:15:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, him. He said he was\Ngoing to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:15:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to help the food digest,\Ngathering up our young men.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:16:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, I can't tell whether\Nyou guys are young or old.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.27,0:16:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all look like old men.\NIs it some sort of curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.61,0:16:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can also fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.24,0:16:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Dwarven warfare, every blow is lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.87,0:16:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our fighting style is to put\Neverything behind one ax strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cleaved the helmet beautifully.\NIt is just like "Jigen."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jige... What? What the heck is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.54,0:16:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Jigen fighting style.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.21,0:16:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was popular among young men \Nin the main branch of the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.05,0:16:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned the Taisha fighting style
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.39,0:16:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because I didn't have much time \Nto learn the Jigen style...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.68,0:16:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how far away your world is\Nfrom ours, your way of thinking is the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.31,0:16:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.40,0:16:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Soldiers exist everywhere\Nregardless of their appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.15,0:16:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.65,0:16:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did they...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.86,0:16:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you? I mean, what the heck are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:17:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They forged an alliance with not only\Nthe Elves but also the Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.16,0:17:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You Drifters are quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never would have expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.88,0:17:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that you would actually\Nmanage to produce a musket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.21,0:17:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How absolutely terrifying!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.55,0:17:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.97,0:17:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, the dirt won't come off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We... We have a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saint-Germi's wagon is outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.35,0:17:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The powerful twinkie count...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.06,0:17:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.52,0:17:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Boobienu. What the hell is he,\Nan entertainer or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.65,0:17:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is Count Saint-Germi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.43,0:17:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is a powerful aristocrat who \Nowns a third of the Orte empire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why are you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.49,0:17:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saint-Germi! Are you a Drifter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.48,0:17:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or as we suspect, are you with the Ends?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.87,0:17:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh dear, you are treating \Nme like I'm criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether you believe me \Nor not, I am a Drifter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.36,0:17:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid enough to believe\Nan End like me actually exists?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:17:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Wh...?!\N--Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.34,0:18:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your breasts are large but\Nnot your brain, you stupid girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.93,0:18:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then, why on earth did you help\N"Father" found an empire like Orte?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you?! Orte is a great empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.77,0:18:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk like it's the work\Nof the Ends, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.90,0:18:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Father," Adolf Hitler,\Nwas also a respectable Drifter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He formed the incredibly\Nefficient bureaucratic government.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.07,0:18:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He eliminated nepotism\Nand centralized the wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.29,0:18:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, he meticulously \Ncrafted a strict hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.58,0:18:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, he unified the people and\Nformed a centralized government...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.96,0:18:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...excluding my reward, \Nwhich is my territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.13,0:18:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did such incredible work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.05,0:18:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, how could we have fought against
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,other races surrounding us for fifty years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, I saw a man who\Nhad the same eyes as yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.43,0:18:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know who he was\Nor what he was talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.90,0:18:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the man stuffed his own tea kettle\Nwith gunpowder and died in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.61,0:18:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was that sort of monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:19:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you talking about Matsunaga Danjo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh dear, you're lumping me in\Nwith the likes of him? How terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he already know about us?\NWe can't let our guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.58,0:19:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what brought you here, Count Saint-Germi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.38,0:19:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to verify that you are\Nworth joining forces with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the leader,\NShimazu Toyohisa, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.18,0:19:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Once again, I can't tell if\Nthe person before me is a man or a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.23,0:19:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?! Are you a man of Orte?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.69,0:19:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I may be a man of Orte...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.44,0:19:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...yet...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.57,0:19:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He read my move!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.91,0:19:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His swordsmanship is great,\Nbut his bloodthirst is weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.03,0:19:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bad. In thirty years,\Nyou would totally be my type.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's nothing I can do about it.\NI am sorry if I end up killing you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would've been dangerous if you\Nwere a bearded elderly veteran.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.86,0:20:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Curse yourself for being young!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.27,0:20:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Allister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.50,0:20:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fulame! I can't take this anymore...\NCan't even stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.30,0:20:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you do this to Allister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.61,0:20:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you and that old man are outside\Nmy strike zone, so I'll be just fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.66,0:20:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you beat me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.25,0:20:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unless a boy with a ponytail \Nand bangs over one eye appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.79,0:20:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyohisa, we have a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My expert subordinates are\Nevaluating your leader by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.26,0:20:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.81,0:20:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.97,0:20:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.31,0:20:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Toyo. What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what is going on,\Nbut I hit him hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.82,0:21:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are many people in this world\Nwhose gender I can't figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.82,0:21:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.41,0:21:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.74,0:21:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A traitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.29,0:21:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to sell off the Orte Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.87,0:21:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can give you a huge discount\Nand a great deal right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The empire...?\N--Sell off...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.05,0:21:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct...\Nwhile it is still worth something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.93,0:21:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a country falls,\Nit must fall in the proper way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.05,0:21:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be unbearable if the armed forces\Nof the other countries invaded Orte
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.77,0:21:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and forced us to sign an instrument\Nof surrender, fracturing the state.
